{
  "texts": [
    "Equation (47) only considers the training and test instances' final feature representations and loss function gradient",
    "Hence, the majority of representer point's computation is forward-pass only and can be sped up using batching.",
    "This translates to representer point being very fast-several orders of magnitude faster than influence functions and Sect. 5.2's dynamic estimators (Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2021).",
    "However, representer points' simplicity comes at a cost.",
    "First, at the end of training, it is uncommon that a model's final linear layer has converged to a stationary point."
  ]
}